# X-Steps AI Composer — Cursor Rules

Full-stack LLM-powered X-Steps AI Composer for pharmaceutical manufacturing (SAP XSteps → PI Sheets).

## Tech Stack
- Frontend: Vue 3 (Composition API) + Vite + Pinia + Vue Router + Tailwind CSS + Axios
- Backend: Node.js + Express + Sequelize v6
- Database: PostgreSQL 16 + pgvector (`vector(1536)` on `xsteps.embedding`)
- LLM: Anthropic Claude (`claude-sonnet-4-20250514`)
- Auth: JWT + bcryptjs
- Import: CSV, Excel (xlsx), JSON, XML (fast-xml-parser), ZIP (adm-zip) — see `docs/specs/IMPORT-SPEC.md`

## Project Layout
- `/server` — Express API, Sequelize models, services, routes, seeders
- `/client` — Vue 3 SPA (operator chat + admin)
- `/docs` — DOCUMENTATION, DEV, specs/, playbooks/
- `/fixtures` — test CSV and images (`fixtures/test-xsteps.csv`)
- `docker-compose.yml` — `pgvector/pgvector:pg16`
- `.env` — `DATABASE_URL`, `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY`, `JWT_SECRET`, `PORT=3000`

## Database Models (6)
User, XStep (embedding vector 1536), PISheet, PISheetStep, PromptConfig, AuditLog

### Associations
- User hasMany XStep, PISheet, PromptConfig, AuditLog
- PISheet belongsTo User; hasMany PISheetStep (CASCADE)
- PISheetStep belongsTo PISheet

## XStep Categories (enum)
Warenbewegung | Rückmeldung | Prozess | Qualität | Dokumentation

## Language
- Operator UI + PI instructions: **German**
- Admin UI: **English**

## npm Scripts (root)
- `dev` — server + client concurrently
- `db:sync` — Sequelize sync + pgvector extension
- `db:seed` — users, 17 XSteps, default PromptConfig
- `db:reset` — drop, sync, seed

## Seed Users
- admin@pisheet.local / admin123 (admin)
- operator@pisheet.local / operator123 (operator)

## Implementation Order
1. DB + models + seed
2. Auth
3. Repository + import (`docs/specs/IMPORT-SPEC.md`)
4. Embeddings + vector search
5. LLM + chat SSE
6. Templates + PDF
7–11. Frontend + polish

## GMP
Always suggest line clearance, IPC, documentation; quality steps need signatures. Generated sheets are **Entwurf** (draft).
